content_vision: I was alone and nobody remembered who I was anymore. Old friends saw my as some opponent of sports. I moved away and felt better
text:
Intro:
An outsider, just a stranger in my own hometown, memories fading,
trying to find my way back to the light.

Verse 1:
I was just a faded memory, forgotten in my own hometown, trying to find my way back to the light,
but with you by my side, everything feels right.
Saw me as an outsider, not part of their exclusive crowd,
but with you, I finally found my place.
But your hand in mine, I feel like I'll never lose my way again,
you bring back the light that once was dim.
But with your hand in mine, I feel like I belong, no longer fading or feeling out of place,
your love is the light that guides me home.

Chorus 1:
But with your love, I found the courage to leave it all behind,
and now I know my worth, no longer fading or feeling out of line.
Your love is the beat that keeps me alive,
no longer fading or feeling out of line.

Verse 2:
But even though I left, memories of my past still linger in my mind,
haunting me with doubts and fears.
But now I've found a new home, where I'm accepted for who I am,
no longer haunted by the past, I can finally breathe again.
But your love was my anchor in the storm, pulling me back to solid ground,
no longer lost and alone, I finally found where I belong.
But with your love by my side, I found the strength to leave it all behind,
no longer held back by the past, I can finally shine.

Chorus 2:
But with you, I found my true identity, no longer fading into obscurity,
you brought me back to life and set me free.
But with you, I found my true identity despite the doubters,
no longer fading into obscurity

Bridge:
But with you, I finally found my way back to the light,
leaving behind the shadows of my old life
But with your love, the faded memories of my past become just a distant blur,
replaced by the brightness of our future.

Outro:
And now with you by my side, I've found my place in this world once again,
no longer an outsider but a loved and cherished part of this new town.
